.\" Man page for mdcat
.\" Automatically generated from help output.
.TH MDCAT 1 "2026-03-06" "mdcat" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mdcat \- cat for markdown: show markdown documents in terminals
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mdcat
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,FILENAMES\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mdcat
reads Markdown files and displays them with syntax highlighting, images,
and terminal formatting where supported. It can read from standard input
when \fI-\fP is given.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-no\-colour\fR
Disable all colours and other styles.
.TP
\fB\-\-columns\fR \fI\,COLUMNS\/\fR
Maximum number of columns to use for output.
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-local\fR
Do not load remote resources like images.
.TP
\fB\-\-fail\fR
Exit immediately if any error occurs processing an input file.
.TP
\fB\-\-detect\-terminal\fR
Print detected terminal name and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-ansi\fR
Skip terminal detection and only use ANSI formatting.
.TP
\fB\-\-completions\fR \fI\,COMPLETIONS\/\fR
Generate completions for a shell to standard output and exit.
Possible values: \fBbash\fR, \fBelvish\fR, \fBfish\fR, \fBpowershell\fR, \fBzsh\fR.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-paginate\fR
Paginate the output of mdcat with a pager like less (default for mdless).
.TP
\fB\-P\fR, \fB\-\-no\-pager\fR
Do not paginate output (default). Overrides an earlier \-\-paginate.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see also \fBman mdcat\fR).
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version information.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mdless (1)
.sp
The program can be installed as or linked to \fBmdless\fR for automatic
pagination.
.SH REPORTING BUGS
Report issues to <https://github.com/swsnr/mdcat>.
